Rating: 4
I used all of the ingredients in this recipe but instead of piling them on a single platter I arranged them on indiviual salad plates for a sit down dinner for six. I placed a rolled piece of prosciutto on top of the sliced tomato, topped that with a round each of mozzarella and hard boiled egg, draped 2 narrow strips of roasted bell pepper (from a jar) over the top, sprinkled green and black olives around the edges, tucked in a whole basil leaf for garnish and sparingly drizzled the basil oil over the whole thing. It made a the most colorful and appetizing presentation on a simple white plate and every single guest asked for the recipe!

