Rating: 4
I made this as an appetizer for a dinner party, as suggested by previous comment, without prosciutto and egg because one of my friends is vegetarian. For vinegar, I added balsamic vinegar and herbs (thyme, basil, oregano), salt and pepper for additional flavor. I cut the tomato and mozzarella cheese into bite size wedges and scattered them on the serving platter topped with roasted pepper and mixed olives. It created a more casual look. Since asparagus is in season, I blanched some and placed it around the platter. The whole dish was colorful and tasty.

Rating: 4
This antipasto was loved at our dinner party, and makes a nice presentation. We also added a little balsamic on top for added color and flavor.

